02/03/2006
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Croatia sent shockwaves through the world of football when it beat Argentina 3-2 in a friendly football match in Basel, Switzerland on Wednesday (1 March). In another warm-up game ahead of the World Cup, Serbia-Montenegro beat Tunisia 1-0. Turkey and the Czech Republic ended their friendly match in a 2-2 draw in Izmir, and Bulgaria beat Macedonia 1-0 in Skopje. The Macedonians have not won a match at home since September 2004. (AFP, Reuters - 01/03/06) 
